suggests a viral cause.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054828,0.072626,0.08278,0.089524,0.090434,0.091826,0.094238,0.091927,0.089368,0.088234,0.080445,0.07377],"unified_progress":[0.051596,0.071022,0.081305,0.088794,0.092743,0.094628,0.094038,0.095441,0.091582,0.088934,0.080143,0.069773]},{"section":11,"text":"The genital ulcers also point towards a viral infection, possibly HSV as well, since HSV can affect the genital area, causing painful ulcers.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043292,0.057888,0.073686,0.083161,0.091174,0.09635,0.099675,0.10168,0.099909,0.094788,0.082942,0.075457],"unified_progress":[0.043485,0.063533,0.080748,0.088904,0.093712,0.10012,0.098845,0.098735,0.09487,0.09033,0.07946,0.067256]},{"section":12,"text":"Now, considering the connection between DVT and these ulcers, I recall that some systemic conditions can lead to both.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046222,0.070318,0.075928,0.082761,0.08447,0.087164,0.092154,0.092888,0.094444,0.09944,0.091851,0.08236],"unified_progress":[0.041698,0.066246,0.077918,0.089542,0.091249,0.092905,0.094741,0.094884,0.092886,0.093391,0.086136,0.078404]},{"section":13,"text":"One condition that comes to mind is antiphospholipid syndrome (APS).","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033048,0.061958,0.078145,0.08818,0.093898,0.097009,0.10109,0.10013,0.097724,0.097065,0.08232,0.069436],"unified_progress":[0.036436,0.067717,0.083265,0.093063,0.096665,0.099661,0.10035,0.098768,0.094915,0.090903,0.077204,0.061051]},{"section":14,"text":"APS is characterized by the presence of antibodies (like lupus anticoagulant) that can cause clotting issues, leading to DVT.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025637,0.045735,0.066269,0.079503,0.09853,0.10828,0.11223,0.11588,0.11247,0.095558,0.076037,0.06387],"unified_progress":[0.031347,0.058927,0.08246,0.094075,0.10151,